\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Ballistics? Are they insane?
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 a shrill voice said through the colonel's intercom.
 She was beginning to feel this would be one of the bad days in the service.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The deafening sound of gunfire filled the wide access corridor.
 Flashes of metal sparks and gun muzzles etched ghost images of the Communion
 death-troops advancing.
 There was no other source of light.
 Colonel Ciarandor had ordered a complete blackout onboard.
 All units were to use IRU modules on their energy carbines.
 They hadn't tried that in the past three weeks.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Communion troops were using hardened kinetic energy rounds, threatening
 to tear the ship apart from the inside out.
 They had never tried that before.
 It was always a bad thing when the enemy smartened up a bit.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Sergeant, you hold that bulkhead for as long as it takes and I'm sending
 you Earthside.
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There was a buzz and a crackle, then the monotone beep of a simple acknowledging
 com-click.
 That sergeant now had a real extra incentive, and the Colonel was known
 to always deliver.
 The huge Keplerian right beside her was grinning widely, watching as the
 Colonel's support squad let off steady-aimed, high-powered shots that slowed
 down the death-squad's advance.
 Still though they came at them with a careless abandon that made their
 name proud.
 Their autorifles on full burst, they drove ever closer to the colonel's
 position, turning the access corridor into a bullet ridden construct that
 looked dangerously frail.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Hanul, I'm afraid we might be able to have some use for your particular
 set of abilities.
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Proud to serve, Colonel.
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Just don't go berserk.
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\end_layout

